\section{Introduction}

Assessment is an essential activity in universities, and it is performed
to evaluate students' academic performance. Quizzes and assignments are
often adopted as assessment tools by teachers to evaluate students'
comprehension of the taught concepts. Usually, these assessments are
manually checked, which might occasionally cause human error and bias in
marking. This might prompt students to question the fairness and
transparency of the assessment and evaluation process.

To avoid this, this project is designed to develop a Fair and Unbiased
Assessment System, which can automatically evaluate students' quizzes
and assignments using artificial intelligence. In this system, students
are required to upload their assessment documents in PDF format, and
based on the uploaded documents, artificial intelligence will
automatically evaluate and calculate the marks according to the answers
provided.

The system will be used by different categories of users, such as
administrators, teachers, and students, and will be used in a university
environment. The administrator will be able to manage different records
such as student registration, teacher details, and course details. The
database will store different pieces of important information such as
student details, course details, assessment files, and marks obtained.

Furthermore, the system will also be able to provide performance reports
for teachers and students. Teachers will be able to view performance
reports for each class, such as class averages, and students will also
be able to view detailed reports for each assessment, such as marks and
mistakes identified by AI.

\section{Problem Statement}

In many universities, instructors grade quizzes and assignments by hand.
While teachers want to assess students fairly, this manual grading can
sometimes lead to bias, whether perceived or real. Factors like a
student's behavior or past interactions with the teacher can
unintentionally affect grading. Even with efforts to be fair, students
may still feel the assessments are biased, which can harm trust in the
evaluation system.

Another major issue is the heavy workload teachers face. In large
classes, instructors must look through many assignments and quizzes
individually. Checking each assessment by hand takes a lot of time and
effort, making the process slow and tiring. This workload also raises
the chances of human error and inconsistency in grading.

Because of all these challenges, there is a need for a system that can
assist instructors in carrying out assessments in a more uniform,
transparent, and efficient manner. An automated system that assesses
student responses through artificial intelligence can help reduce the
workload for instructors and at the same time minimize biases in
grading.

\section{Objectives}

The main objectives of the proposed Fair and Unbiased Assessment System
are as follows:

\begin{enumerate}[label=\arabic*.]
    \item Development of a centralized database system that would manage and
    store information regarding students, faculty members, courses, and
    assessment in a systematic way.
    
    \item Automate the evaluation of quizzes and assignments by analyzing PDF
    files using artificial intelligence techniques.
    
    \item Minimize the possibility of biased and inconsistent results by
    reducing human intervention in the marking of assignments and
    quizzes.
    
    \item Reduce the workload of instructors by using this system to
    automatically evaluate assignments instead of manual evaluation.
    
    \item Manage assessment information in a systematic way, including
    uploaded documents, earned marks, and calculated percentages.
    
    \item Generate detailed reports regarding students' and teachers'
    performance, including marks earned in individual questions,
    mistakes committed by students, and results of the assessment.
    
    \item Provide class-level performance analysis and class performance
    reports for teachers.
\end{enumerate}

\section{Scope}

The scope of this fair and unbiased assessment system used in
educational institution. This system will store data of academic
assessment data in secure and organized way to support fair evaluation
of students. The database will store the data related to students,
faculty, administration, courses, assessments, submission and evaluation
report which will create by the AI system (But the AI part handle
manually by us). The database will provide a centralized system to store
and retrieve data efficiently.

The scope of system includes:

\begin{itemize}
    \item The system will maintain the record of students, faculty and
    administration authentications
    
    \item It will manage the course enrollment data assign to faculty and
    students
    
    \item It creates sections of assessments like quizzes, assignments.
    
    \item It keeps the record of student submissions in the form of pdf.
    
    \item It stores the result of assessment, quizzes.
    
    \item It will keep the data safe and secure from unauthorized users through
    relational database constraints.
\end{itemize}

The system main focus will be on database design, data storage and data
management using MY SQL. It will store the data related to the entities
and provide data whenever require from database with the help of MySQL.

